Body: Description: an employee on our team upgraded our version. Now we don't have the option to manually add people to the resource groups. Need assistance asap. Thank you.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Mike Candon, Brady Mellenthin

Next Steps Updated: +++++
2025_0515: Must review the meeting
+++++

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Step 1: Upgrade the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor to version 12.0.0.1051.  
Step 2: Navigate to the Access Information Center within the Resource Audit feature.  
Step 3: Attempt to manually add individuals to resource groups.  
Step 4: Observe that the option to manually add people to resource groups is no longer available.

@Mike Candon​ the customer's leadership asked for this to be escalated to management. Please tag me here after you send the meeting summary and update the summary fields.

@Stacy Petruzzi​

What We've Learned Updated: 1) Back in AIC 11.6.0.37 under Home > "Resource Ownership" (with the correct permissions) there was a "Change Access" button with which one could "Change Resource Access" (Add, Remove, Change resource access).

2) Also in AIC 11.6.0.37, on the "Change Resource Access" popup the end user could "SET [a] DATE" for temporary access that would expire on that date.  This temporary access functionality seems to be missing in AIC 12.0.0.1051.

3) And there was a column on the Home > Access Requests screen called "Expired" which would show the "Access will expire <DATE>" upon mouseover.

4) See the attached screenshots in the 2 folders:
+++++
"SFC_445101_SS_AIC_11.6.0.37_2025_0516"
"AIC_12.0.0.1051_Screenshots"
+++++

Steps to Reproduce Updated: 1) Log into AIC 12.0.0.1051 with an account that has an Administrator role.
2) Navigate to Home > "Resource Owners"
3) Click on the "Resource Audit" button.
4) Edit Group Membership on the right-hand side.
5) On the "Group Memebership Changes" popup, click the "ADD" button.
6) On the "Add Membership Change" popup, type in and "Select [the] Group".
7) Click Next to select the "Change Type".
8) Search at th top to "Add Members" and then click "OK".
9) The former "SET DATE" functionality (and "Expired" column) are no lnoger present.
10) See the attahced screenshots in the folders:
